[2026-07-04T00:50:00] TASK 0.2 — COMPLETE
Did: wrote `/CONTRACTS.md` at repo root pinning three shapes: (1) the
segmented-abstract response for `GET /api/v1/papers/{pmid}/abstract` —
a single ordered `segments[]` array (not separate display/spoken lists)
where each segment carries `index` (the §6.5 sync signal the playback
engine keys highlighting off), `kind` (`section_header`|`sentence`),
`section_label`, `display_text`/`spoken_text`, `char_start`/`char_end`
(§6.5's displayCharRange), and `pause_class` (`structural`|`sentence`,
§6.4); (2) the API error shape `{"error":{"code","message"}}` (§10.3)
with a pinned-but-extensible table of known `code` values including
`service_unavailable` (§13.6) and `rate_limited` (§10.5, deliberately
distinct codes since one is external-dependency downtime and the other
is LitList's own inbound throttling); (3) the Zotero push per-item shape
for `POST /api/v1/zotero/push` (§8.6/8.7) — a `results[]` array of
per-PMID `{pmid, status, zotero_item_key?, error?}`, explicitly never an
all-or-nothing response, with `error` reusing the pinned error shape's
inner object.
Decision calls made (SPEC.md states behavior, not literal JSON field
names, so these were mine to pin — reasoning inline in CONTRACTS.md
too): (a) one unified `segments[]` array rather than parallel
display/spoken arrays, because §6.5's sync mechanism is explicitly
index-based ("the currently-playing utterance's index tells the UI
exactly which sentence to highlight") — a single array makes that
literal; (b) section headers modeled as their own `segment` with
`kind: "section_header"` rather than folded into the following
sentence's text, since §7.5 describes them as spoken as their own short
utterance before their section, i.e. their own pause/utterance boundary;
(c) `rate_limited` (429, caller-side) kept as a separate code from
`service_unavailable` (503, external-dependency-side) since §13.6
explicitly distinguishes these as different problems needing different
user-facing copy, and Task 4C's job is to keep that distinction visible.
Worked: this is a contracts document, not code — no test suite of its
own; its "test" is that Tier 1 (1D)/Tier 2 (2D)/Tier 3 (3A/3B/3D)/
Tier 4 (4A/4B/4C) all build against it without needing to invent or
renegotiate a shape, which later tiers will confirm.
Changed: `CONTRACTS.md` (new file, repo root).
Open: none. Flagging for the orchestrator: per BuildPlan.md's standing
procedure, any future change to this file must (1) be logged here with
reason, (2) grep every build.log for citations of the changed shape, and
(3) get a scoped fix task dispatched per affected already-merged
consumer before that tier's exit gate closes.

